name: Elise Swopes
tweet: I was depressed, suicidal, anxiety ridden, and afraid of everything. I finally figured out I was the key to change and took responsibility. I’ll never regret that acceptance for as long as I live. I opened my mind to the possibilities and the possibilities opened for me.

name: Elise Swopes
tweet: Change can be painful. It’s a consistent mourning and loss. You are not who you will be tomorrow or the next day. Everything dies. So, how are you learning to mourn every change in your life? How does your body react?

name: Elise Swopes
tweet: Our bodies can become our own enemy. The comfort of chemicals released. The comfort of stress. The comfort of repeated negative cycles. Ask yourself, for real... am I doing enough for me? We all know when we’re not. It’s time to be honest.
